{{see|Xerox}}

==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈziɹ.ɑks/}}
*Schoolbook Phonetics: (zērʹäks)
*Last Resort Phonetics: ZEER-ox

===Etymology===
From ''[[Xerox]]'', a photocopier, via ''[[xerography]]'' from Greek ''xero'' meaning “dry” and ''graphy'' meaning “writing”

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# {{slang}} A [[photocopy]].
#: ''Hand me that '''xerox''', would you?''

====Usage notes====
This term may have trademark status. According to Xerox Corporation, ''Xerox'' is properly used only as a brand name to identify the company’s products and services.

====Derived terms====
* [[xerox copy]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|xerox|es}}

# {{slang}} To make a paper [[copy]] or copies by means of a [[photocopier]].
#: ''I '''xeroxed''' the report for all the people at the meeting.''

====Usage notes====
The Xerox trademark is at risk of becoming generic because of this use. The company is engaged in an ongoing campaign to convince the public that this term should not be used as a verb.

